The Market Intelligence team for Workforce Staffing applies science, data and insights to optimize hiring for Amazonâ€™s largest candidate population â€“ Tier 1 Associates. Amazon's hourly workforce brings the magic of Amazonâ€™s industry-leading customer fulfillment to life. The pace at which job creation, hiring, and growth must happen to support the scale and complexity of Amazon businesses is a problem Amazon is uniquely qualified to solve and innovate on. Workforce Staffing literally hires by the hundreds of thousands across multiple business lines, job types, and shift configurations. The Market Intelligence team in particular focuses on applying labor market, competitor, and candidate preference intelligence to enhance job offerings, mitigate operational risk, and sustain Amazon position in the market. Come join a team that is continually shaping and writing the future of the hourly worker landscape.
 
What is the role?
 The Senior Product Manager - Technical, owns the product roadmap and execution for a new market intelligence tool that will diagnose the market health of different locales, provide insights and recommendations, and labor planning guidance to operators, centralized teams, and senior Operational leadership. You will partner closely with a science team, data engineering, and software development teams to deliver transformational data products and insights. This will arm field operators with standardized intelligence to make critical decisions quickly armed with science-based analysis. This tool will enable operators and operational leadership to think holistically about the labor market, in a way that sustains the market health of the hourly workforce for Amazon jobs.
 
 
 Serial experience launching technical products from inception to stable release 
